comment.author: 52583849@N04
comment._content: Aircraft in front is the RAE Hurricane G-EBHS, and in rear is Parnall Pixie II G-EBKM - possibly for the Grosvenor Cup Race on the 4th October 1924. The Parnall was the favorite for the race until its prop parted company with the hub and it had to make a forced landing (where it was reunited with its prop thanks to a small boy - however a different prop had to be used, and performance suffered accordingly).
